{
  "stem": "1033.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "My grandfather had big red moustache, and it was twirled.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "He looked fierce.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And occasionally he winked at me during the prayer.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Otherwise, the whole thing was almost surreal.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Then there was a wonderful cat, I remember, in the-- we had a cat, a little red cat.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I used to torture him, for which now I apologize.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But-- it-- and the roosters made wonderful noises.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "It was a-- it was a village life.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "In the orphanage, I-- I always had an ambivalent feeling about God.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "I was overridden by the notion of sin and having said God's name in vain, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And in the orphanage-- it must've been the first few months, there was a synagogue in the orphanage-- I remember walking into the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "There was nobody there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And I used to be afraid of the synagogue, and I told God that that was not a fair deal that I got.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And I was not going to be afraid any longer.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And I can't tell you what a huge relief that was, to have done this.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And eventually I made friends in the orphanage, and eventually I became myself a big boy, and other little kids looked up to me.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And it was like a family, like a huge, wonderful, extended family.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And I still keep in touch with some of them who live in Israel and other places.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my grandparents-- I used to, in 19-- 1940, 1941 and '42, I did summer holidays I spent on the farm.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And by then, they took away the farm from them, because they were Jews.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But they opted to-- to remain in the building, so they had one room of their house where they lived in.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
